{"title_page": "Stoney Creek (Delaware River tributary)", "text_new": "{{Infobox river\n| name               = Stoney Creek\n| name_native        = \n| name_native_lang   = \n| name_other         = \n| name_etymology     = \n| nickname           =\n<!---------------------- IMAGE--> \n| image              = \n| image_size         = \n| image_caption      = \n| image_alt          = \n<!---------------------- MAPS --> \n| map                = \n| map_size           = 180\n| map_caption        = Confluence of Stoney Creek and Delaware River\n| map_alt            = Map of the confluence of Stoney Creek and Delaware River\n| pushpin_map        = Pennsylvania\n| pushpin_map_size   = 180\n| pushpin_map_caption= \n| pushpin_map_alt    = Location of the confluence of Stoney Creek and Delaware River\n<!---------------------- LOCATION -->\n| subdivision_type1  = Country\n| subdivision_name1  = United States\n| subdivision_type2  = State\n| subdivision_name2  = Pennsylvania\n| subdivision_type3  = County\n| subdivision_name3  = Delaware County\n<!---------------------- PHYSICAL CHARACTERISTICS -->\n| length             = \n| width_min          = \n| width_avg          = \n| width_max          = \n| depth_min          = \n| depth_avg          = \n| depth_max          = \n| discharge1_location= \n| discharge1_min     = \n| discharge1_avg     = \n| discharge1_max     = \n<!---------------------- BASIN FEATURES -->\n| source1            = \n| source1_location   = Chester Township, Pennsylvania\n| source1_coordinates= {{coord|39|50|57|N|75|24|27|W|display=inline}}<ref name = USGS>{{cite web |title= ID 1188751 Stoney Creek |url = https://geonames.usgs.gov/apex/f?p=138:3:0::NO:3:P3_FID,P3_TITLE:1188751,Stoney%20Creek |website=geonames.usgs.gov |accessdate=19 May 2019}}</ref>\n| source1_elevation  = \n| mouth              = \n| mouth_location     = [[Port of Chester]]\n| mouth_coordinates  = {{coord|39|49|17|N|75|23|47|W|display=inline}}<ref name = USGS/>\n| mouth_elevation    = sea level (0 ft.)\n| progression        = \n| river_system       = Delaware River\n| basin_size         = \n| basin_landmarks    = \n| basin_population   = \n| tributaries_left   = \n| tributaries_right  = \n| waterbodies        = \n| waterfalls         = \n| bridges            = \n| ports              = \n| custom_label       = \n| custom_data        = \n| extra              = \n}}\n\n'''Stoney Creek'''  is a [[tributary]] of the [[Delaware River]] in southeast [[Delaware County, Pennsylvania|Delaware County]] in [[Pennsylvania]], United States. The stream rises in [[Chester Township, Delaware County, Pennsylvania|Chester Township]], and flows through [[Chester, Pennsylvania|City of Chester]] and [[Trainer, Pennsylvania|Trainer]], at times creating their border. It discharges at the [[Port of Chester]] on the northern perimeter of the [[Trainer Refinery]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.delcopa.gov/planning/pubs/DelRiverWatershedConservationPlan.pdf|title=Delaware River Watershed Conservation Plan for the Delaware River Corridor and Naamans, Marcus Hook, and Stoney Creek Watersheds Delaware County Planning Department September 2015|publisher=|accessdate=25 May 2019}}</ref> and south of Stoney Creek Yard. Historically it has been known a Middle Run and Stoney Run.<ref name=\"epa.gov\">{{cite web|url=https://cumulis.epa.gov/supercpad/SiteProfiles/index.cfm?fuseaction=second.Cleanup&id=0300939#bkground|title=METRO CONTAINER CORPORATION Site Profile|website=cumulis.epa.gov|accessdate=27 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Crossings==\nThe creek lends its name to the [[Stoney Creek Secondary]], a rail line operated by [[Conrail Shared Assets Operations]] as part of the South Jersey/Philadelphia Shared Assets Area, and serves as contract local carrier and switching company for both [[CSX Transportation]] and the [[Norfolk Southern Railway]]. The [[Philadelphia Subdivision]] of CSX Transportation also bridges the creek.\n\nThe [[Wilmington/Newark Line]], one of the 13  [[commuter rail]] line lines in [[SEPTA|SEPTA's]] [[SEPTA Regional Rail]] network, traverses the creek.   Originally built by the [[Philadelphia, Wilmington and Baltimore Railroad]], it is now part of the [[Northeast Corridor]].\n\n[[Interstate 95 in Pennsylvania|Delaware Expressway]] (I-95) and [[U.S. Route 13 in Pennsylvania|U.S. Route 13]] also traverse the creek.\n\n==Wastewater and pollutants==\nStony Creek Technologies was a company that discharged into the creek.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://response.epa.gov/site/site_profile.aspx?site_id=2921|title=Site Profile - Stoney Creek Technologies - EPA OSC Response|website=response.epa.gov|accessdate=26 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://energytrendswatch.com/2019/01/14/third-circuit-holds-new-property-owner-on-the-hook-for-old-cleanup-costs/|title=Third Circuit Holds New Property Owner on the Hook for Old Cleanup Costs|first=Author Blank Rome|last=LLP|date=14 January 2019|publisher=|accessdate=26 May 2019}}</ref> The company later sold he site adjacent to the creek. Federal courts found that the new property owners must pay for environmental cleanup costs that occurred before they acquired it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blogs.findlaw.com/third_circuit/2018/10/new-property-owners-must-pay-environmental-cleanup.html|title=New Property Owners Must Pay Environmental Cleanup|website=Findlaw|accessdate=26 May 2019}}</ref><ref>http://www2.ca3.uscourts.gov/opinarch/172607p.pdf</ref> The so-called Metro Container site along the creek is a [[Superfund Site]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://response.epa.gov/site/site_profile.aspx?site_id=2098|title=Site Profile - Metro Container Corporation - EPA OSC Response|website=response.epa.gov|accessdate=27 May 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"epa.gov\"/><ref>https://www.atsdr.cdc.gov/HAC/pha/MetroContainerNPLSite/MetroContainerNPLSiteHC02082013.pdf</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.environmentalleader.com/2015/10/exxon-bp-10-others-pay-3-5m-clean-up-hazardous-waste-at-superfund-site/|title=Exxon, BP, 10 Others Pay $3.5M, Clean Up Hazardous Waste at Superfund Site|first=Jessica Lyons|last=Hardcastle|date=21 October 2015|publisher=|accessdate=27 May 2019}}</ref> The Trainer Refinery makes use of the creek for [[wastewater]] and pollutant discharges,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.state.nj.us/drbc/library/documents/dockets/061219/1986-041-3draft.pdf|title=PMDOCKET NO. D-1986-041-3 DELAWARE RIVER BASIN COMMISSION Monroe Energy LLCTrainer Refinery Industrial Wastewater Treatment Plant Borough of Trainer, Delaware County, Pennsylvania May 1, 2019|publisher=|accessdate=26 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://files.dep.state.pa.us/Water/Wastewater%20Management/EDMRPortalFiles/Permits/PA0012637_NPDES_PERMIT_20181113_Final_V13.pdf|title=AUTHORIZATION TO DISCHARGE UNDER THE NATIONAL POLLUTANT DISCHARGE ELIMINATION SYSTEM DISCHARGE REQUIREMENTS FOR INDUSTRIAL WASTEWATER FACILITIES December 1, 2018|publisher=|accessdate=26 May 2019}}</ref> which have sometimes exceeded permissible amounts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://digital.olivesoftware.com/Olive/ODN/PhiladelphiaInquirer/shared/ShowArticle.aspx?doc=PHQP/2018/03/28&entity=Ar00200&sk=B6DC0A79&mode=text|title=Pa. high in excessive pollution discharges - Philadelphia Inquirer - Philly Edition, 3/28/2018|website=digital.olivesoftware.com|accessdate=27 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://pennenvironment.org/news/pac/facilities-pa-rank-second-highest-nation-exceeding-water-pollution-standards|title=Facilities in PA rank second highest in nation for exceeding water pollution standards|website=pennenvironment.org|accessdate=27 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Delaware River tributaries]]\n* [[List of rivers of Pennsylvania]]\n* [[Stony Creek (Susquehanna River tributary)]]\n* [[Stonycreek River]] in Pennsylvania\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cite web|url=http://easternpaseagrant.org/Chester/delawarecntywatershedsflood.html|title=Chester City Adaptation Opportunity Areas \u2013 Delaware County Watersheds |website=easternpaseagrant.org|accessdate=25 May 2019}}\n*[https://www.chesco.org/DocumentCenter/View/7267/watersheds_of_chescoletteraug06?bidId= Watersheds of Chester County]\n\n[[Category:Rivers of Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:Tributaries of the Delaware River]]\n[[Category:Rivers of Delaware County, Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:Chester, Pennsylvania]]\n\n\n{{Pennsylvania-river-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox river\n| name               = Stoney Creek\n| name_native        = \n| name_native_lang   = \n| name_other         = \n| name_etymology     = \n| nickname           =\n<!---------------------- IMAGE--> \n| image              = \n| image_size         = \n| image_caption      = \n| image_alt          = \n<!---------------------- MAPS --> \n| map                = \n| map_size           = 180\n| map_caption        = Confluence of Stoney Creek and Delaware River\n| map_alt            = Map of the confluence of Stoney Creek and Delaware River\n| pushpin_map        = Pennsylvania\n| pushpin_map_size   = 180\n| pushpin_map_caption= \n| pushpin_map_alt    = Location of the confluence of Stoney Creek and Delaware River\n<!---------------------- LOCATION -->\n| subdivision_type1  = Country\n| subdivision_name1  = United States\n| subdivision_type2  = State\n| subdivision_name2  = Pennsylvania\n| subdivision_type3  = County\n| subdivision_name3  = Delaware County\n<!---------------------- PHYSICAL CHARACTERISTICS -->\n| length             = \n| width_min          = \n| width_avg          = \n| width_max          = \n| depth_min          = \n| depth_avg          = \n| depth_max          = \n| discharge1_location= \n| discharge1_min     = \n| discharge1_avg     = \n| discharge1_max     = \n<!---------------------- BASIN FEATURES -->\n| source1            = \n| source1_location   = Chester Township, Pennsylvania\n| source1_coordinates= {{coord|39|50|57|N|75|24|27|W|display=inline}}<ref name = USGS>{{cite web |title= ID 1188751 Stoney Creek |url = https://geoname